quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  25,33,And they bring you no similitude but We reveal the truth and the best interpretation thereof (or a better argument)
  25,34,"They who shall be gathered upon their faces into hell, such are worse in plight and further from the path"
  25,35,"And We did give to Moses the Book, and placed with him his brother, Aaron, as a minister (or Priest)"
  25,36,"And We said, \"Go you together to the people who have denied Our revelations. Then We destroyed them with utter destruction"
  25,37,"And the people of Noah, when they denied the messenger, We drowned them, and made them a sign for mankind. We prepared for the wrongdoers a grievous woe"
  25,38,"And (the tribes of) A´ad and Thamud and the people of Ar´Rass, and many generations between them"
  25,39,"For each of them We set forth parables and examples, and each one have We utterly ruined"
  25,40,"Indeed, they have come past the cities which were rained on with an evil rain; have they not seen them? Nay, but they fear not the Resurrection (or hope not for resurrection)"
  25,41,"And when they see you (Muhammad) they only took you for a jest, \"Is this he whom Allah has sent as a Messenger"
  25,42,"He well-nigh leads us astray from our gods, had we not been constant to them.\" But they shall know, when they see the torment, who errs most from the path"
  25,43,"Have you considered him who takes for his god his own lusts (prejudices, fantasies, superstitions)? Would you then be guardian over him"